This paper is primarily focused on the emergence of language through deep reinforcement learning agents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the study of evolutionary linguistics, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SD (Software Development). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cultural dynamics in language emergence, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
